===2010 census===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0651470|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715032025/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0651470|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Nipinnawasee CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Nipinnawasee had a population of 475. The population density was {{convert|155.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Nipinnawasee was 422 (88.8%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2 (0.4%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 9 (1.9%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 3 (0.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 39 (8.2%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 50 persons (10.5%).

The Census reported that 475 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 192 households, out of which 47 (24.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 126 (65.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 15 (7.8%) had a female householder with no husband present, 9 (4.7%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 9 (4.7%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 33 households (17.2%) were made up of individuals, and 11 (5.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.47.  There were 150 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (78.1% of all households); the average family size was 2.68.

The population was spread out, with 90 people (18.9%) under the age of 18, 35 people (7.4%) aged 18 to 24, 74 people (15.6%) aged 25 to 44, 177 people (37.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 99 people (20.8%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 49.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.1 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 90.6 males.

There were 217 housing units at an average density of {{convert|70.9|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 144 (75.0%) were owner-occupied, and 48 (25.0%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 1.4%; the rental vacancy rate was 11.1%.  337 people (70.9% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 138 people (29.1%) lived in rental housing units.

